Update References to Visualforce Pages Served on Salesforce.com
The new default behavior of the <apex:sectionHeader> component makes Visualforce pages secure by default.
Updated Default Behavior of Visualforce Section Header Components
The description attribute now only evaluates commonly used, secure HTML elements.
Visualforce pages, templates, and components with <apex:sectionHeader> are protected against cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks.
